                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/487: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 28, 1929—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>394. Associated Press despatch from Moscow printed in today’s papers say China
                    has accepted Russian terms for settlement Chinese Eastern Railway controversy.
                    Can you confirm?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
